In August 2011, the President of the United States, Barack Obama, had phone calls with French President Nicolas Sarkozy and German Chancellor Angela Merkel to discuss the eurozone crisis and the situation in Syria. The President commended the leadership of both leaders in addressing the economic challenges in Europe and discussed the importance of implementing the steps agreed upon in the July 21 summit. They also condemned the Syrian regime's use of violence against its people and expressed support for additional measures to pressure the Assad regime and assist the Syrian people.